More composed. Entry good but admits it wasn’t a true signal; took it based on strong bearish momentum (WAE/histogram flip/dead zone) + ES bearish. Target at lower VWAP band; TP placement good. Feels it ticked boxes and executed well.

Good entry signal and momentum down. Not prepared / skipped pre-trade prep (influenced by previous trade). Finished in profit, but believes sticking to rules could have reached another TP. Not in right mindset to trade.

Not a great trade. Wasn't really prepared. Promised myself I wouldn't trade in the New York session but entered anyway. Impatient. If I'd let the trade play out and kept stop loss and take profit, it would likely have finished profitable. Not prepared and shouldn't have entered.

Second short/add-on as part of the same bearish momentum move. Added contract when bearish momentum/ WAE histogram strengthened. Managed per plan and exited at the 1.5R target. Good discipline after earlier mistake; closed charts afterwards to protect the day.

Short. After T80 mistake, stayed patient and waited for clear bearish Hulk candle. Entered on signal; bearish momentum strong and WAE histogram pushed down. Added another contract as momentum confirmed. Felt nervous on shorts but followed process on autopilot. Took clean 1.5R target; helped finish day green.

Worst trade of the day. Forced it. Missed original entry off VWAP band due to hesitation (long upper wick + massive bearish Hulk candle). Then hesitated/second-guessed and entered right at the top trying to catch next 5-min swing high; it reversed and stopped me out unnecessarily. Should not have taken this trade.

T79: Tried to catch the re-entry long to take session highs. Not ideal entry; cautious because this setup has reversed on me before, so I used a very tight stop. Price chopped and made a new session high but my trade didn’t quite play out. Risk was small; execution and management were good.

NQ long retest of upper VWAP band. Clear entry signal; strong Hulk candles; WAE strong. Entry and management good. Moved SL to BE then retrace stopped out; afterwards price continued to TP. Trend strong but range/chop (typical Monday).

GCG6 long with bullish trend but at upper VWAP band/volatility. Prior candle bearish HALT; entry was strong bullish HALT. Used stop-entry above nearest 1-min fractal high to confirm bullish momentum. Once in profit with a clear close, moved SL to BE; choppy pullback stopped at BE. Process/execution good.

NQ short. Not a true entry signal (no bearish Hulk candle). Took it based on ES pushing down fast + WAE volume/flip; aiming for quick flush down to mid VWAP. Overall trend felt bullish so kept SL tight; stopped at breakeven. Composed; execution ok but setup quality lower.

Management/execution/composure good. Moved SL to BE once in profit. Didn’t reach full 1.5R TP; bullish overall trend/stop-hunt/retrace.

Good signal incl. 5-min close; bearish Hulk candle close after volatility/stop-hunt then move down. Used slightly bigger SL expecting retrace; placed near nearest fractal high. Price didn’t follow through to take prior lows; didn’t move SL to BE to give room, took small loss. Composure/execution good; followed plan.

First trade of session. Upper VWAP band reaction/reversal candle; WAE not above dead zone but reversal setup. Broker/market entry error caused late entry, worsened R:R, tight stop. Stopped at breakeven. Composure and execution good given issue.

Lucky to spot this trade as I was completing the notes for the previous trades. Noticed significantly large bearish candle. At first, had the mentality of not wanting to enter as I had just had a win and didn't want to lose profits. Managed to overcome and enter anyway. Entry was good as I was patient, waited for entry candle to retrace first, then saw volatility to the downside so made my entry then. This helped improve RR as I was then able to place SL above upper VWAP band - as price was more likely to continue its bearish momentum. Emotional state - wasn't confident and flowing. Felt fear of losing money, also had to remind myself to let the trade play out. Even though I wanted to close the trade early and take profit, I had to keep reminding myself that I am already in profit, and that whatever comes from this is a bonus.

In review, the entry candle is as close to an A+ set up as we can be. First positioning box represents ideal entry, the other represents actual entry. Happy that I was able to react quickly after loss and then execute again. Emotions were fine. I think I felt focused and locked in. In hindsight, potentially risked too much, however I was very tight with SL - closer than typical entry for this strategy. This does pose the question about my max DD for the day.

Sometimes this works, however with shorts, especially fading a bullish trend, it's always better to protect account. Emotions were calm and focused for most of the trade. Then a little bit of confusion and stress about where to place my SL.

No clear entry signal and at the time of the trade, I don't think I recognized what I do now. Happy that I entered, however it was more for the wrong reasons, rather than the underlying confluences. Still a revenge trade, however the question remains, if this trade didn't play out, would I be able to handle the loss mentally? Would I switch to TILT mode? Most likely yes. Which is why it is important that I keep my emotions in check. Also this renewed sense of purpose. Strengthen the connection as to why I am doing this, why it is important to not resort to TILT and blowing accounts for the sake of being 'right'. I have to remember this is for Dad. The same old patterns will never allow me to achieve what I want. I need to think and behave differently.

Feel a bit fucked off. Missed the first trade and from there just kept getting stopped out. Very frustrating. Price is currently very choppy, best decision would be to walk away. reviews.ai_insight: Week 2025-12-15 to 2025-12-21: Net +1845.00 on 39 trades with 51.3% win rate, but Efficiency Score 0.54 (below 2.0 target) and Cost of Errors -1085.00 show a profitable week achieved with significant self-inflicted leakage. Notes show two modes: when executing well you are patient and let trades work; when impatience appears you force entries without signal, trade chop, and can slide into tilt (notably 2025-12-17: repeated ‘no signal/forced’ entries -> chasing -> breaking session rules -> trading until lockout/DD). Another recurring theme is inconsistency in protection/management when right (hesitation to move stop to BE) and P/L-protection psychology (fear of giving back profits leading to hesitation, then later forcing). Priority is eliminating ‘no-signal’ trades and having pre-decided management rules to prevent the impatience-to-tilt cascade.
reviews.user_reflection: Although I had mistakes and moments of weakness / poor trading etc. I'm glad in the end that I was able to overcome them and end up net positive. So many times previous, I had let negative days affect me so badly that it would just get continually worse - eventually failing multiple challenges etc. Now I feel like I'm really focused on learning to 'lose' so to speak, making mistakes but remembering that they will happen and I just need to focus on being consistent and doing the right things, day in day out. Next week I want to continue this pattern and become even better than last week in terms of composure, execution etc.

reviews.ai_insight: Strong day in process and emotional control: repeated notes of calm, patience, and composure aligned with high efficiency (3.67) and zero cost of errors. You executed a consistent thesis (Asia low) and accepted when the flush didn’t materialize via disciplined BE management. Watch the one potential crack: resizing/adding because “risk wasn’t enough.” Ensure scaling rules are pre-defined rather than emotion-led. Keep using BE as a confirmation-based protection tool, not as discomfort avoidance.
reviews.user_reflection: Thoughts for today follows much of what was said in the trade notes. Felt on point, felt composed and just ready to trade. Not overly emotional. I hope to keep the mind frame and composure for next session, and the session after that. Eventually let it be my baseline and really start getting consistent with my trading.

reviews.ai_insight: Net profitable week but very low efficiency (0.36 vs target >2.0), suggesting overtrading/chop exposure and entries not aligned with core strategy. Notes indicate a pattern: missing an early trade triggers urgency/chasing, followed by repeated stop-outs; awareness of needing to walk away but continuing to trade; and revenge trading rationalized as “confluence.” Key risk is emotional escalation after a losing day leading to TILT and historically large drawdowns/account damage. Primary focus: protect mindset first—implement a mandatory reset protocol after missed trades or first significant emotional spike; prioritize selectivity and execution quality over participation.
reviews.user_reflection: Yes definitely felt this. I have noticed that I can trade ok and be profitable for a few days, even weeks, however I am not trading effciently or inline with my strategy. Then I have a losing day, which typically sets me off and I end up on TILT. Often blowing my account. My goals for next week are to keep composed, keep consistent, focus on execution and being a 'professional trader' who understands the market isn't about winning, its about process, day in day out.
